---+++ Round-Table Virtual Organization Reports and Issues:

   * Report from Collective VO Representatives
   * Ongoing Goals/Milestones 
   * Planning for the Future

%BLUE% *minutes:*

*Doug:* STAR is working at MIT with condor team to use GLOW for condor VM submission. This is a work in progress.

*Piotr:* SBGRID has been scaling up its usage in the last month with a peak of 3600 and a continuous level of 12 in the last week. Some issues with Match-Maker reported. They are looking at the possibility of using Panda scheduler.

*Horst:* DOSAR is planning a workshop in Johannesburg and has invited Kent to give an OSG talk.

*Brad:* DZERO has a new production release and is now seeing 10Million events per week. They are looking at LCG for opportunistic resources. Ruth reported that DZERO is now submitting to LCG through OSG interfaces. This could be considered by other VOs if there is an interest.

*Rick:* CDF is running well. There is a proposal by the experiment to reprocess a significant fraction of the data. There is a need for access to the data handling systems at FNAL. Starting to think about how to use opportunistic storage.

*Tom:* Collective VO/NYSGrid, nothing else for the collective VO, things going well with NYSGrid

*Shaowen:* Collective VO/CIGI, nothing else for collective VO, new release of software with OSG interfaces. Participated in a workshop with high visibility in the NSF called cyber-GI workshop.

*Kent:* LIGO has worked hard to address issues with submission for the E@OSG application, while also scaling up to more sites. This resulted in this application becoming the top user of the OSG for the past two weeks in summary. Chander reported that the science credits for E@H is now seeing its largest single contribution from OSG, about 3 billion credits per day. Kent reported that there was a lot of hands on effort to get this to this level. This is causing stress on NFS at sites and there will need to be effort to adapt to this level of stress from this heavy of a load on sites.

*Paul:* Happy to see the production levels up!

%ENDCOLOR%

